2004", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC3851.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document defines Secure/Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (S/MIME) version 3.1.  S/MIME provides a consistent way to send and receive secure MIME data.  Digital signatures provide authentication, message integrity, and non-repudiation with proof of origin.  Encryption provides data confidentiality.  Compression can be used to reduce data size.  This document obsoletes RFC 2633. [STANDARDS-TRACK]"];
