Securing Header Fields with S/MIME
2015", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC7508.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document describes how the S/MIME protocol can be extended in order to secure message header fields defined in RFC 5322.  This technology provides security services such as data integrity, non-repudiation, and confidentiality.  This extension is referred to as 'Secure Headers'."];
